				p HTML/SCSS, Ruby on Rails, Slim Lang, Twitter Bootstrap, Github, Illustrator, After Effects
section.portfolio-info#info
	.container-fluid.px-md-0
		.row.justify-content-between.g-0.mx-md-0
			.summary.col-12.col-md-4.position-sticky.d-flex.align-items-center.vh-100.mx-auto.top-0
				.flex-grow-1.py-8.py-md-10
					h2 Project Details
					h6
						span.badge.text-bg-secondary Problem
					p As a brand-new product, Jumpix needed a clear user experience, intuitive interface, and a strong digital presence to introduce the platform to customers. The team required UX, UI, and front-end development support, along with user documentation and marketing materials, to help users understand how the product worked and why it mattered.
					h6
						span.badge.text-bg-secondary Process
					p I collaborated closely with the CTO to help bring Jumpix from concept to launch. Using Ruby on Rails, SCSS, JavaScript, and Slim, I designed and developed the customer-facing interface and shaped the overall user experience. I created mockups for the main website, designed custom iconography, and ensured the product was accessible and intuitive. To support onboarding and engagement, I produced detailed user guides and created animated marketing videos to communicate key features and value.
					h6
						span.badge.text-bg-secondary Outcome
					p Jumpix launched with a cohesive, user-friendly interface and a polished digital presence. The refined UX, clear documentation, and supporting marketing materials helped users quickly understand the platform, boosting engagement and supporting a smooth rollout for the new product.
